  "A 50 kg person stands at one end of a 4 m long, 100 kg boat floating on still water. The person walks 3 m toward the other end. How far does the boat move relative to the water?": "",
  "No external horizontal force, so x_cm stays fixed. If person moves +3 m relative to boat, and boat moves -d: person displacement = 3 - d, boat displacement = -d. 50(3-d) + 100(-d) = 0. 150 - 50d - 100d = 0. 150d = 150. d = 1 m.": "",
  "A 10 kg firework moving upward at 30 m/s explodes into two pieces. A 3 kg piece continues upward at 60 m/s. Where is the center of mass 2 seconds after the explosion relative to the explosion point? (Use g = 10 m/s²)": "",
  "80 m above": "",
  "60 m above": "",
  "20 m above": "",
  "40 m above": "",
  "The CM continues as if no explosion: v_cm = 30 m/s upward, with gravity. y_cm = v_cm(t) - ½gt² = 30(2) - ½(10)(4) = 60 - 20 = 40 m above the explosion point.": "",
